Vuelta Velogames Daily Update

Race Results - Stage 20


Here’s the non-spoiler 4min highlight clip on Youtube:

https://youtu.be/GGIb2WT9lkE










In the final test for GC contenders it was El Pistolero who both fired the shots and collected the bounty on the villainous slopes of the Angliru. The greatest rider of his generation was finally able to orchestrate a deserving bookend to his career in his final race with a stage victory. In wet conditions Alberto took off at the start of the final climb with his team mate Pantano, reeling in all the breakaway to cross the finish line victoriously in first position. He was followed only 20 seconds later by the hard charging SKY duo of Wout Poels and Chris Froome, effectively securing for Froome the overall win and the amazing Vuelta/TDF double. VIncenzo Nibali lost time but still holds on to third place overall.
